Blackstone Alternative Investment Advisors LLC


                  Blackstone Alternative Investment Advisors (BAIA) participates in a broad range of instruments, markets and asset classes economically tied to US and foreign markets. Investments may include, but are not limited to, equity securities, fixed income securities and derivative and commodity instruments. The equity securities in which the BAIA Funds may invest include equity securities of companies of any market-cap throughout the world, which may include common stock, convertible securities, depositary receipts, exchange traded funds, real estate investment trusts, royalty trusts, and partnership interests. BAIA allocates the assets of the BAIA Funds among a variety of non-traditional  and alternative investment strategies through allocations to underlying managers that serve as investment sub-advisors and investments in underlying investment vehicles. These strategies may include, but are not limited to: Fundamental, Global Macro, Opportunistic Trading, Quantitative, Managed Futures and Multi-Strategy.                




Chairman & Chief Executive Officer of the Blackstone Group

                                    Tenure Unconfirmed                


Blackstone Alternative Asset Management LP


                  From a top-down perspective, Blackstone Alternative Asset Management (BAAM) focuses on positioning funds to capitalize on market opportunities through focused research and allocation of resources. From a bottom-up perspective, the firm seeks to build deep relationships with underlying hedge fund managers that are strengthened by their investment professionals' relevant experience in the financial markets, as well as the Blackstone network in other alternative asset classes.Their funds' strategies generally allocate capital to a diversified group of portfolio (i.e., hedge fund) managers that invest or trade in a wide variety of securities and other instruments, including, but not limited to, equities and fixed-income securities, currencies, commodities, futures contracts, options and other derivative instruments, all of which may be listed or unlisted, rated or unrated, distressed or publicly or privately issued. BAAM Funds also may invest in separate managed accounts with underlying managers. In general, BAAM offers 3 types of products: (1) commingled funds (2) customized funds (3) advisory clients.BAAM employs various types of investment strategies including broadly diversified and strategy focused. Their strategy focuses strategies include: (1) equity: fundamental, opportunistic trading, top down, private equity and quantitative long/short (2) credit: opportunistic, relative value, mortgages and structured/asset back securities (3) corporate distressed (4) leveraged loans (5) event-driven (5) direct origination (6) reinsurance (7) hedging (8) managed futures (9) commodities (10) interest rates and (11) emerging markets.                




Chairman & Chief Executive Officer of the Blackstone Group

                                    Tenure Unconfirmed                


Blackstone Alternative Solutions LLC


