Blackstone Senfina Advisors LLC


                  Blackstone Senfina Advisors (BSA) primarily provides investment advisory services to private investment funds (BSA Funds), which mainly allocate capital to third-party portfolio managers (BSA Portfolio Managers). The BSA Portfolio Managers may invest and trade, on margin or otherwise, in debt and equity securities and other financial instruments, including derivatives. The BSA Portfolio Managers generally will manage capital exclusively for the BSA Funds during an initial investment period, although they may manage capital for BSA affiliates during such exclusivity period. Thereafter, the BSA Portfolio Managers may invest capital for other investors through a hedge fund and/or managed account platform. BSA also directly manages and trades a portion of the BSA Master Fund’s assets in a sub-account of the BSA Master Fund (the Center Book) and uses a hedge account designed to achieve a market-neutral profile in aggregate for the BSA Funds. In their management of the Center Book, BSA invests and trades, on margin or otherwise, directly in debt and equity securities and other financial instruments including derivatives.BSA allocates the BSA Funds’ capital to BSA Portfolio Managers that pursue a range of investment strategies and invest in various securities and financial instruments. The firm seeks  to take advantage of investment opportunities across asset classes and sectors. BSA’s primary goal is to identify the right talent pool of BSA Portfolio Managers, without specific diversification requirements or limitations.                




