Blackstone Alternative Investment Advisors LLC

                    Blackstone Alternative Investment Advisors (BAIA) participates in a broad range of instruments, markets and asset classes economically tied to US and foreign markets. Investments may include, but are not limited to, equity securities, fixed income securities and derivative and commodity instruments. The equity securities in which the BAIA Funds may invest include equity securities of companies of any market-cap throughout the world, which may include common stock, convertible securities, depositary receipts, exchange traded funds, real estate investment trusts, royalty trusts, and partnership interests. BAIA allocates the assets of the BAIA Funds among a variety of non-traditional  and alternative investment strategies through allocations to underlying managers that serve as investment sub-advisors and investments in underlying investment vehicles. These strategies may include, but are not limited to: Fundamental, Global Macro, Opportunistic Trading, Quantitative, Managed Futures and Multi-Strategy.                  




